    <main class="container mx-auto px-6 py-8 md:py-16">

        <!-- Disclaimer -->
        <div class="bg-red-100 border-l-4 border-red-500 text-red-800 p-6 rounded-lg mb-12 shadow-md" role="alert">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">A Necessary Disclaimer</h3>
            <p class="text-base">I am not a medical professional. This website shares my personal story and the research I did to find answers for myself. The information here is not medical advice. Please do not stop or change any treatment plan without consulting your qualified medical doctor. My goal is to share a story of hope and encourage you to become an empowered partner in your own healthcare journey.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Hero Section -->
        <section id="home" class="text-center mb-20 md:mb-32">
            <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 leading-tight">I Solved My 20-Year Mystery Illness.</h2>
            <p class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-lg md:text-xl text-slate-600">
                For over two decades, I lived with a diagnosis of schizophrenia. After years of personal investigation, I discovered an unexpected physical cause that medication couldn't touch. This is my story, and a guide to help you put on your own detective hat.
            </p>

            <div class="mt-12">
                <!-- IMPROVEMENT: Suggestion for a more dynamic video. -->
                <!-- Consider making a short, personal video introducing your journey. Authenticity is key. -->
                <div class="bg-slate-200 aspect-video max-w-3xl mx-auto rounded-lg shadow-lg flex items-center justify-center">
                    <p class="text-slate-500 font-semibold">[ Your 2-Minute Introduction Video ]</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- IMPROVEMENT: "Who This Is For" section to connect with the audience -->
        <section id="for-you" class="mb-20 md:mb-32 bg-blue-50 p-8 rounded-lg text-center">
             <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Is This Journey for You?</h2>
             <p class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-slate-700 text-lg">This story is for anyone who has ever felt that their diagnosis doesn't tell the whole story. It's for those who have a persistent feeling that something has been missed, and for the loved ones who support them on their search for answers.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- My Story Section -->
        <section id="story" class="mb-20 md:mb-32">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8 text-center">My Story: The Winding Path</h2>
            <div class="space-y-16">
                <!-- Part 1: The Diagnosis -->
                <div class="md:grid grid-cols-5 gap-12 items-center">
                    <div class="col-span-2 bg-slate-200 h-64 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-6 md:mb-0 shadow">
                        <img src="https://1ink.us/images/thediagnosis.png" alt="A modern, calm medical clinic waiting room." class="w-full h-full object-cover rounded-lg shadow-md">
                        <p class="text-slate-500" aria-hidden="true"></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-span-3">
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2 text-blue-700">Part 1: A Label and a Life Sentence</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-lg">It began with symptoms that defied easy explanation. When doctors gave me the diagnosis of schizophrenia, it felt like a final answer. I accepted it, believing the complex medication regimen was my only path forward, even though it only managed the symptoms, never resolving them.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Part 2: Environmental Clues -->
                <div class="md:grid grid-cols-5 gap-12 items-center">
                    <div class="col-span-3 md:order-2">
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2 text-blue-700">Part 2: The First Clues</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-lg">Years later, I started noticing things that didn't fit the official narrative. Learning about the old mine on our property, I began to wonder about the dust, the soil, the very air I was breathing. A small voice asked: could the answer be *outside* of me? This was the true beginning of my detective work. I started taking small precautions, like always wearing <strong class="text-slate-700">waterproof boots</strong> to create a barrier against whatever might be in the ground.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-span-2 md:order-1 h-64 mb-6 md:mb-0">
                        <img src="https://1ink.us/images/thefirstclues.png" alt="Flowering branches with a rustic shed and green foliage in the background, representing the home environment." class="w-full h-full object-cover rounded-lg shadow-md">
                        <p class="text-slate-500" aria-hidden="true"></p>

                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Part 3: Dead Ends -->
                <div class="md:grid grid-cols-5 gap-12 items-center">
                    <div class="col-span-2 bg-slate-200 h-64 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-6 md:mb-0 shadow">
                        <img src="https://1ink.us/images/therabbitholes.webp" alt="A modern, calm medical clinic waiting room." class="w-full h-full object-cover rounded-lg shadow-md">
                        <p class="text-slate-500" aria-hidden="true"></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-span-3">
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2 text-blue-700">Part 3: The Rabbit Holes</h3>
                        <!-- IMPROVEMENT: Made the "spore cloud" detail a powerful, standalone sentence. -->
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-lg">My investigation was a maze of dead ends. I researched poisonous spiders, millipedes, and cyanide from the mine. I became obsessed with mold, observing how disturbing bat guano or rotten wood could release a <strong class="text-slate-700">dense, almost pressurized cloud of spores</strong> with a single footstep. It seemed the threat wasn't just present; it was reactive. Each dead end, however, taught me how to be a better investigator.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Part 4: The Breakthrough -->
                <div class="md:grid grid-cols-5 gap-12 items-center">
                    <div class="col-span-3 md:order-2">
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2 text-blue-700">Part 4: The Rosetta Stone</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-lg">The breakthrough came from the most unexpected place: a routine tetanus vaccine. The shift was immediate and profound. The fog that had clouded my existence for twenty years began to lift. This event became my "Rosetta Stone"â€”the key that unlocked everything. To understand my working theory, <a href="#breakthrough" class="text-blue-600 font-semibold hover:underline">I've dedicated a full section to it here.</a></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-span-2 md:order-1 bg-slate-200 h-64 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-6 md:mb-0 shadow">
                        <img src="https://1ink.us/images/therosettastone.png" alt="A modern, calm medical clinic waiting room." class="w-full h-full object-cover rounded-lg shadow-md">
                        <p class="text-slate-500" aria-hidden="true"></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- The Investigator's Toolkit Section -->
        <section id="toolkit" class="mb-20 md:mb-32">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8 text-center">The Investigator's Toolkit</h2>
            <p class="text-center text-slate-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12">This is not a diagnostic tool. It's a guide to help you collect clues and organize your thoughts before speaking with your doctor. Think of yourself as a detective building a case file for your own health.</p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                <!-- Environment Card -->
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-t-4 border-emerald-500">
                    <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                        <!-- IMPROVEMENT: Added SVG Icon -->
                        <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-emerald-500 mr-3" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8.25 21v-4.875c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125V21m0 0h4.5V3.545M12.75 21h7.5V10.75M2.25 21h1.5m18 0h-18M2.25 9l4.5-1.636M18.75 3l-1.5.545m0 6.205l3 1m-3-1l-3-1m3 1v5.5" /></svg>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-emerald-800">Your Environment</h3>
                    </div>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600">
                        <li>What is the history of my home and the land it's on?</li>
                        <li>Could there be hidden mold, lead, or industrial waste?</li>
                        <li>Are my symptoms worse in certain locations or seasons?</li>
                        <li>What is the air and water quality like in my area?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <!-- Physical Health Card -->
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-t-4 border-sky-500">
                     <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                        <!-- IMPROVEMENT: Added SVG Icon -->
                        <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-sky-500 mr-3" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 4.5v15m7.5-7.5h-15" /></svg>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sky-800">Your Physical Health</h3>
                    </div>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600">
                        <li>Do physical symptoms accompany my primary diagnosis?</li>
                        <li>Have I had a full medical workup recently?</li>
                        <li>What is my full medical history (infections, injuries)?</li>
                        <li>How do diet, sleep, or stress affect my symptoms?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <!-- Diagnosis Card -->
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border-t-4 border-purple-500">
                    <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                        <!-- IMPROVEMENT: Added SVG Icon -->
                        <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-purple-500 mr-3" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9.879 7.519c1.171-1.025 3.071-1.025 4.242 0 1.172 1.025 1.172 2.687 0 3.712-.203.179-.43.326-.67.442-.745.361-1.45.999-1.964 1.769a.75.75 0 01-1.214-.882c.512-.77.94-1.532 1.214-2.324a13.535 13.535 0 00-.442-1.087.75.75 0 01.317-1.043zM12 15.75a.75.75 0 01.75-.75h.008a.75.75 0 01.75.75v.008a.75.75 0 01-.75.75h-.008a.75.75 0 01-.75-.75v-.008z" /></svg>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-purple-800">Your Diagnosis</h3>
                    </div>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600">
                        <li>Have my symptoms changed or evolved over time?</li>
                        <li>Does my experience perfectly match the textbook definition?</li>
                        <li>How have I responded to past and current medications?</li>
                        <li>Have I sought a second or third medical opinion?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- The Breakthrough Clue Section -->
        <section id="breakthrough" class="mb-20 md:mb-32 bg-white p-8 md:p-12 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
             <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2 text-center">The Breakthrough Clue</h2>
             <p class="text-center text-slate-500 font-medium mb-8">A Deeper Look at My "Tetanus Theory"</p>
             <div class="bg-amber-100 border-l-4 border-amber-500 text-amber-900 p-4 rounded-md mb-8 text-sm">
                <strong>Personal Hypothesis, Not Medical Advice:</strong> This section details my theory for my unique situation. It's meant to illustrate a line of investigative thinking, not to suggest a diagnosis or cure.
            </div>
            <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6 text-slate-700">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-800">Connecting the Dots: Bacterium and Environment</h3>
                    <p>After the dramatic change I experienced, I researched the bacterium the tetanus vaccine targets: <em>Clostridium tetani</em>. It's found everywhere in soil and dust, and it produces a potent neurotoxin. Given that I was living on land with an old mine and constant dust exposure, this became my primary suspect.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-800">My Hypothesis: Chronic Exposure vs. Acute Infection</h3>
                    <p>What if my symptoms were not from a primary psychiatric condition, but the neurological effects of chronic, low-level exposure to this environmental neurotoxin? An acute infection causes classic tetanus (lockjaw). But perhaps a constant, low-grade exposure, over years, could produce chronic, atypical neurological symptoms that mimic mental illness.</p>
                    <p>In this theory, the vaccine finally gave my immune system the specific tools it needed to neutralize the toxin that had been affecting my system for years. The message isn't about one specific vaccine, but about the importance of thinking "outside the box" and considering overlooked environmental pathogens with your doctor.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-800">Resources for Your Own Investigation</h3>
                     <!-- IMPROVEMENT: Added accessibility hints for external links -->
                     <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                         <li><a href="https://www.cdc.gov/tetanus/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">CDC Page on Tetanus<span class="sr-only"> (opens in new tab)</span></a></li>
                         <li><a href="https://www.who.int/news-room/fact-sheets/detail/tetanus" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">WHO Page on Tetanus<span class="sr-only"> (opens in new tab)</span></a></li>
                         <li><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term=infection+induced+psychosis" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">PubMed: "Infection Induced Psychosis"<span class="sr-only"> (opens in new tab)</span></a></li>
                     </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- How to Talk to Your Doctor Section -->
        <section id="doctor" class="mb-20 md:mb-32">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8 text-center">How to Talk to Your Doctor</h2>
            <p class="text-center text-slate-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12">Advocating for yourself can be intimidating. Remember, your doctor is your most important partner. The goal is to collaborate, not confront. Here are some phrases you can adapt to start the conversation:</p>
            <div class="space-y-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
                <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 bg-white p-6 rounded-r-lg shadow-md italic">
                    <p>"I've been tracking my symptoms and environment closely, and I'd like to partner with you to explore if there could be any underlying physical causes we haven't considered."</p>
                </blockquote>
                <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 bg-white p-6 rounded-r-lg shadow-md italic">
                    <p>"Given my living situation, I have some concerns about potential environmental exposures. Could we run some tests to rule out factors like heavy metal toxicity or chronic infections?"</p>
                </blockquote>
                <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 bg-white p-6 rounded-r-lg shadow-md italic">
                    <p>"To be thorough, I would feel more confident if we could do a full medical workup to rule out other possibilities. What would you recommend we start with?"</p>
                </blockquote>
            </div>
        </section>

    </main>

